message: formatting
Minor changes. Formatting.
Nationality is important. Why hide it?

So many people make an effort to change history. There was a clear division in Poland by nationality of people living there. SM was a Jew. Or a Polish Jew at least. Nobody is proud of him but that's up to Jews to face.
Salmon Morel was Jewish by nationality
SM was Jewish by nationality. He had Polish citizenship. And then he gained Israeli one. So his nationality was Jewish.
No, Salmon Morel is not of Jewish background. He was Jewish. He happened to have Polish citizenship. If he was Polish of Jewish background then so were all the Holocaust victims.
Comma

This fact that he was a Jew is highly important because for many decades Morel's action, genocide on Germans, were perceived as a permissible revenge on Germans for Holocaust. Genocide for genocide that is.

It is historically incorrect to deny Jewish colaboration with Germans in Holocaust through the Judenrats. The sources added are for that reason. No historian can dispute the claims that Kurek is making.  Also Kurek has three decades of solid research of Holocaust sources in Yiddish. Her views are commonly accepted views amongst historians that know these sources, especially as they are Jewish ones and come right from the Ghetto.

Reverting as in the previous form the article is historically and factually incorrect - it is based on biased sources hence adding more sources to give a broader view on what Judeopolinia is. It's not a myth.
No evidence exists to prove that German forces were not involved in the Jedwabne masacre - removing this as it does not make any sense.
Minimum wage and income tax thresholds are two distinct concepts and should not be confused. Removing the line about minimum wage.
